{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a415bf1b-0692-404c-9c02-f699bc6f91ab","content":"The template is **not quite ready** to publish. Here are the issues:\n\n### Missing required field\n- **`$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for tooling validation.\n\n### Recommended additions\n| Field | Why |\n|-------|-----|\n| `groupIdentity` | Needed if you plan multiple language/framework variants. |\n| `precedence` | Helps resolve conflicts when multiple versions are installed. |\n| `description` | NuGet listing will be bare without it. |\n| `defaultName` | Controls the default project name (`dotnet new mywebapi`). |\n\n### Other observations\n- `identity` still uses the placeholder \"MyCompany\" — replace with your real package prefix.\n- The `Framework` symbol is defined but never wired to a `replaces` or framework choice in a `.csproj` — verify the template substitution actually works.\n- No `preferNameDirectory` set (defaults to `false`).\n\n**Minimum fix to be publishable:** add `$schema` and a `description`. Everything else is strongly recommended but not blocking.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"62ddca1f-5d17-470d-bd49-80a132d8a56d","outputTokens":261,"requestId":"A785:D40E:162FB57:18C7890:6A051F54"},"id":"cc243836-dfdd-4d73-93a5-511903d20fea","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:03:25.154Z","parentId":"1d67dd3e-1657-4d24-97b0-2712357bc759"}
